snippet.textDisplay:
Omg it's all so beautifully crafted, to the point that I'd consider getting married just to have something a little like that. I love that you two did the Adam's family dance, you guys kind of embody that weirdness and romance. And man...on the subject of the gooey lovey dovey nonsense...well when you two had your first look and all you could truly convey to each other was "I love you" I cried so much. We all see your goofball sides alone and together all the time. And it was nice that you left some of the emotional bits in. If those are what you left in, I cant imagine how emotional and strong and connected the parts you kept between each other, and in front of your loved ones at the wedding must be!

I also love that you found a way for your cat to "be there" in a way that makes all of you happy. Its something that were I in a similar situation, would feel weird that my cat wasnt somehow a part of it, because he would be an integral part of the everyday and any relationship I would have. You really put a lot of heart into those details, and if you treat your marriage everyday like you have treated your wedding, you will be as fulfilled and loved for the rest of your lives as you were on your wedding no matter any missing shoes and floppy soles you come across.

I'll leave you with this quote from a book about a girl in space since it fits the theme of the wedding:

"But the truth is, the longer you love the same person, the more mysterious they become. March is like a pocket universe, full of stars, and I will never learn all his light."
May there be many more adventures to come.

"
